Thomas F. "Mack" McLarty, III






Former White House Chief of Staff, Counselor to the President, and Special Envoy for the Americas under President Bill ClintonThomas F. "Mack" McLarty, III is chairman and founder of McLarty Associates and chairman of the McLarty Companies, a fourth-generation family transportation business based in Little Rock, Ark. He held various roles advising three U.S. presidents: Bill Clinton, George H. W. Bush and Jimmy Carter. 




